CodeSystem: HIVExtendedCodes
Id: HIVExtendedCodes
Title: "HIV Extended Codes"
Description: "Codes defined only in this Implementation Guide and require mapping to a standard semantic terminology."
* #First-time "First-time user of ART" "Client is ART naive, having never taken ART to treat HIV before"
* #Restarting "Restarting ART" "Client is restarting ART after stopping treatment for any reason"
* #Routine "Routine viral load test" "Routine refers to viral load tests obtained at standard intervals following ART initiation to monitor viral load response to ART"
* #Targeted "Targeted viral load monitoring" "Targeted refers to viral load tests obtained based on a specific clinical indication (such as concern about disease progression or failure to respond to ART)"
